OL,4,CMost Indians oppose interfaith
OL,5,Cmarriage, survey shows
OL,6, Most Indians see themselves and their
OL,7, country as religiously tolerant but are
OL,8, against interfaith marriage, a survey
OL,9, from Pew Research Center has found.
OL,11,FPeople across different faiths in the
OL,12,Fcountry said stopping interfaith
OL,13,Fmarriage was a "high priority" for
OL,14,Fthem.
OL,16,FThe research comes follows laws
OL,17,Fintroduced in several Indian states
OL,18,Fthat criminalise interfaith love.
OL,20,FPew interviewed 30,000 people across
OL,21,FIndia in 17 languages for the study.
